Name: codeExecutor
Description: Execute code snippets in common local languages and shells.
Version: 1.0

Overview:
This toolset runs code in a selected language and returns stdout/stderr and
exit code. It is useful for quick calculations, scripts, and shell commands.

Commands:
- list_languages
  List supported languages.

- execute_code
  Execute a code snippet.
  Parameters:
  - language (string, required): python | java | c | cpp | js | html | css | cmd | powershell
  - code (string, required): The code to execute.
  - args (array, optional): Command-line args.
  - stdin (string, optional): stdin content.
  - timeout (integer, optional): Timeout in seconds. Default 10.
  - cwd (string, optional): Working directory.
  - env (object, optional): Environment variables to add/override.

- execute_file
  Execute a code file by language.
  Parameters:
  - language (string, required): python | java | c | cpp | js | cmd | powershell
  - path (string, required): File path.
  - args (array, optional): Command-line args.
  - stdin (string, optional): stdin content.
  - timeout (integer, optional): Timeout in seconds. Default 10.
  - cwd (string, optional): Working directory.
  - env (object, optional): Environment variables to add/override.

Usage Examples:
- list_languages
- execute_code language="python" code="print('hi')"
- execute_code language="java" code="public class Main{public static void main(String[]a){System.out.println(\"hi\");}}"
- execute_code language="c" code="#include <stdio.h>\nint main(){printf(\"hi\\n\");return 0;}"
- execute_code language="cpp" code="#include <iostream>\nint main(){std::cout<<\"hi\\n\";}"
- execute_code language="js" code="console.log('hi')"
- execute_code language="html" code="<h1>Hello</h1>"
- execute_code language="css" code="body{background:#eee;}"
- execute_code language="cmd" code="dir"
- execute_code language="powershell" code="$PSVersionTable"
- execute_file language="python" path="script.py" args=["--help"]

Behavior Notes:
- Python/Java/C/C++/JS are executed if the required compiler/runtime exists in PATH.
- HTML/CSS are saved to a temporary file and the path is returned.
- Output includes stdout, stderr, and exit code.

Dependencies:
- Python interpreter available in PATH for python execution
- Java (javac/java) for Java execution
- C/C++ compiler (cl or gcc/g++) for C/C++ execution
- Node.js for JS execution
- Windows cmd.exe and powershell.exe
